annotationA: Putative Dol-P-Glc:Glc(2)Man(9)GlcNAc(2)-PP-Dol alpha-1,2-glucosyltransferase; Adds the third glucose residue to the lipid-linked oligosaccharide precursor for N-linked glycosylation. Transfers glucose from dolichyl phosphate glucose (Dol-P-Glc) onto the lipid-linked oligosaccharide Glc(2)Man(9)GlcNAc(2)-PP-Dol (By similarity); Belongs to the ALG10 glucosyltransferase family
annotationB: CG1518, isoform A; Oligosaccharyl transferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: wing disc development; protein glycosylation; chaeta development
